Spain Delays 6 Billion Euro Rail Contract, Expansion Reports

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-03-01T07:02:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/spain-delays-6-billion-euro-rail-contract-expansion-reports.html
  Spain ’s  Finance Ministry  is delaying
a project to build a 6 billion euro ($8.3 billion) high-speed
rail line between Valladolid and Galicia because of fears it
will have an impact on the country’s deficit,  Expansion  said.  The Finance Ministry has not yet approved the project and
is delaying the tendering of contracts to build the rail link
proposed by Jose Blanco, Spain’s minister of transport and
development, the newspaper said, citing unidentified sources at
the Development Ministry.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net . 